{"type":"message","id":"b7db1db7","parentId":"9ba8559c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T23:45:18.437Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I can see the issue now. The markets are showing midpoint as 0.5 with wide spreads (0.98-0.998), which means they're not showing actual price movements. The yes_price and no_price are different, but the midpoint calculation seems to be showing 0.5.\n\nLooking at the data, I can see some markets with actual activity:\n1. \"Will Donald Trump visit Alaska in 2026?\" has volume of 1802.198524 and liquidity of 2519.1352\n2. \"Ukraine election called by March 31, 2026?\" has volume of 237312.671626 and liquidity of 12777.4883\n3. \"Zelenskyy out as Ukraine president by March 31, 2026?\" has volume of 476012.808045 and liquidity of 12705.44947\n\nHowever, the midpoint is still showing as 0.5. This suggests the database might have stale or incorrect midpoint calculations. Let me check the history for one of these active markets to see if there's actual price movement:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_PeQcwAdXX2O4GsbVLQ5C8VoF","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/skills/market-scarper && source venv/bin/activate && python3 -m polymarket_tools get_market_trends 0xdab71ad1d7d7661435f2556eb8e29473d322d9d8af2705a9732c4872629de090 --limit 10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":7828,"output":345,"cacheRead":29568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37741,"cost":{"input":2.19184e-9,"output":1.4489999999999999e-10,"cacheRead":8.27904e-10,"cacheWrite":0,"total":3.1646440000000004e-9}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773618302495}}
