{"type":"message","id":"530e8350","parentId":"3018a557","timestamp":"2026-03-15T23:45:39.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the issue clearly! The midpoint calculation in the database is wrong. When yes_price is 0.993 and no_price is 0.007, the actual midpoint should be around 0.5 (average of bid and ask), but the database is storing it as 0.5 even when the prices are different. This is a data quality issue.\n\nHowever, I can see there's real trading activity. The last_trade_price shows movement from 0.982 to 0.014 to 0.993, etc. This means there IS price movement, but the midpoint field in the database is incorrect.\n\nAccording to SOUL.md, I need to proceed with the \"Cold Start\" fallback. Let me manually analyze markets using the Alpha Playbook strategies. I'll look for markets with:\n1. Volume shocks (high volume relative to average)\n2. Breakouts (price movements >10%)\n3. Spread anomalies\n4. Information drift\n5. Ghost awakens (low liquidity with sudden price moves)\n\nLet me search for markets with high volume first:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3WW8XII180l3dBaF8PuCTyej","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/skills/market-scarper && source venv/bin/activate && python3 -c \"\nimport sqlite3\nimport pandas as pd\nconn = sqlite3.connect('polymarket.db')\n\n# Get markets with highest volume in latest change\nquery = '''\nSELECT \n    m.market_id,\n    m.question,\n    m.slug,\n    mc.volume,\n    mc.liquidity,\n    mc.last_trade_price,\n    mc.datetime\nFROM markets m\nJOIN market_change mc ON m.change_id = mc.change_id\nWHERE LOWER(m.status) = 'active'\nAND mc.volume > 1000\nORDER BY mc.volume DESC\nLIMIT 20\n'''\n\ndf = pd.read_sql(query, conn)\nprint('Markets with volume > 1000:')\nprint(df[['question', 'volume', 'liquidity', 'last_trade_price']].to_string())\nconn.close()\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":1691,"output":463,"cacheRead":37696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39850,"cost":{"input":4.7348e-10,"output":1.9446e-10,"cacheRead":1.055488e-9,"cacheWrite":0,"total":1.7234279999999999e-9}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773618318925}}
