{"type":"message","id":"9128316d","parentId":"fc8e41a0","timestamp":"2026-03-15T23:46:14.613Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the issue with the data. The midpoint is incorrectly calculated as 0.5, but I can see the last_trade_price moving from 0.79 to 0.139 - that's a massive price drop of about 82%! This is a classic \"Breakout\" according to the Alpha Playbook.\n\nLet me manually analyze markets using SQL to find actionable opportunities. I'll look for:\n1. Recent price movements >10% (breakouts)\n2. High volume relative to liquidity\n3. Markets with liquidity between $500 and $2000 (mid-volume mandate)"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_k8BsHgRKg7G8r2WMMvtgDKmf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/skills/market-scarper && source venv/bin/activate && python3 -c \"\nimport sqlite3\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nconn = sqlite3.connect('polymarket.db')\n\n# Get markets with recent price movements\n# We'll look at the last trade price changes over time\nquery = '''\nWITH recent_changes AS (\n    SELECT \n        market_id,\n        last_trade_price,\n        datetime,\n        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY market_id ORDER BY datetime DESC) as rn\n    FROM market_change\n    WHERE last_trade_price IS NOT NULL\n    AND datetime >= datetime('now', '-3 days')\n),\nprice_changes AS (\n    SELECT \n        r1.market_id,\n        r1.last_trade_price as current_price,\n        r2.last_trade_price as previous_price,\n        r1.datetime as current_time,\n        r2.datetime as previous_time,\n        (r1.last_trade_price - r2.last_trade_price) / NULLIF(r2.last_trade_price, 0) as pct_change\n    FROM recent_changes r1\n    JOIN recent_changes r2 ON r1.market_id = r2.market_id AND r1.rn = 1 AND r2.rn = 2\n    WHERE ABS(r1.last_trade_price - r2.last_trade_price) > 0.01  # Minimum 1% change\n)\nSELECT \n    m.market_id,\n    m.question,\n    m.slug,\n    pc.current_price,\n    pc.previous_price,\n    ROUND(pc.pct_change * 100, 2) as pct_change_percent,\n    mc.volume,\n    mc.liquidity,\n    mc.datetime as last_update\nFROM price_changes pc\nJOIN markets m ON pc.market_id = m.market_id\nJOIN market_change mc ON m.change_id = mc.change_id\nWHERE LOWER(m.status) = 'active'\nAND ABS(pc.pct_change) > 0.10  # 10%+ price change\nAND (mc.liquidity BETWEEN 500 AND 10000 OR mc.liquidity IS NULL)  # Mid-volume range\nORDER BY ABS(pc.pct_change) DESC\nLIMIT 30\n'''\n\ndf = pd.read_sql(query, conn)\nprint('Markets with >10% price changes in last 3 days (mid-volume):')\nprint(df[['question', 'current_price', 'previous_price', 'pct_change_percent', 'volume', 'liquidity']].to_string())\nconn.close()\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":1839,"output":724,"cacheRead":40704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43267,"cost":{"input":5.1492e-10,"output":3.0408e-10,"cacheRead":1.139712e-9,"cacheWrite":0,"total":1.958712e-9}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773618347985}}
