{"type":"message","id":"f64f7926","parentId":"ffe12dcf","timestamp":"2026-03-20T14:28:14.282Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the first line says \"0\" which is the line count from wc. The actual data starts from the second line. The issue is that my script is reading the first line \"0\" as a market ID. Let me fix that by skipping empty lines and non-hex lines.\n\nActually, let me check the raw_ids.txt file directly to see the format:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue - there's a \"0\" at the start from `wc -l`. Let me clean and recreate the raw_ids.txt file properly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0c4705e54d2a4875a1dab478","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/relevant_markets && cp raw_ids.txt raw_ids_backup.txt && grep -E '^0x' raw_ids_backup.txt > raw_ids.txt && wc -l raw_ids.txt"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":113036,"output":263,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113299,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774016889304}}
