alysis. Current `batch_runner.py` session is `glow-kelp`.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Goal\nRank the most promising Polymarket markets (exactly 90), run the prediction engine, and create a comprehensive report as requested.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Create a report with exactly 90 markets.\n- Run the prediction engine after ranking.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Wrote and executed ranking script (`/home/boldplane/.openclaw/workspace/rank_markets.py`).\n- [x] Analyzed 5428 active markets from `polymarket.db`.\n- [x] Ranked and selected exactly 90 markets based on quantitative scoring and Alpha Playbook strategies.\n- [x] Created intelligence report: `/home/boldplane/.openclaw/workspace/relevant_markets/intelligence_report_2026-03-20.txt`.\n- [x] Saved market IDs for prediction engine: `/home/boldplane/.openclaw/workspace/relevant_markets/raw_ids.txt`.\n- [x] Initialized Master Arbitrage Ledger (`setup_ledger.py`).\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Running the prediction engine.\n\n### Blocked\n(none)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Simplified Alpha Playbook strategies**: Used current metrics (volume, liquidity, spread, price) as proxies for historical analysis due to initial execution errors.\n- **Fixed script execution method**: Wrote Python script to a file to avoid shell escaping issues encountered in inline commands.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Run the prediction engine on the 90 selected market IDs.\n2. Ensure prediction outputs are integrated or saved appropriately.\n3. Verify the final report includes prediction engine results if required.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Top 5 markets by total score (examples):\n    1. \"Russia-Ukraine Ceasefire before GTA VI?\" (Score: 165)\n    2. \"Puffpaw FDV above $50M one day after launch?\" (Score: 155)\n    3. \"Puffpaw FDV above $100M one day after launch?\" (Score: 155)\n    4. \"Will George Russell be the 2026 F1 Drivers' Champion?\" (Score: 155)\n    5. \"Will Ken Paxton win the 2026 Texas Republican Primary?\" (